svg.text: To create a centralized platform to manage restaurant operations smoothly.
- A single dashboard to display all orders from multiple sources to ease off the process of tackling multiple orders.
- Complete basic operations like bill creation and stock management.

g.text: Conducted preliminary interviews with different types of restaurants i.e. Fine Dining, Cafe, Casual Dining,Quick Service Restaurants.
This was essential so as to find our first target customer.
Interviews were conducted in 25 restaurants in GTB Nagar and Noida sector 38.
This was the idea validation step. Understanding whether the usefulness of the one dashboard feature was of profound importance.
Formulated the questionnaire. The following are some of the snippets. Have a look at the entire questionnaire here.

svg.text: What kind of a POS system are you using currently? Since how long and what made you switch?
Get to know the competitors as well as the features that made a user switch to the current product.
How do you manage orders from multiple sources? Explain the process.
Core Question. Validates our value proposition.
Explain the process of creating an order.
Understanding the screenflow to conduct a single task.

The user has a different app for each source i.e. Zomato, Swiggy, Foodpanda.
In addition there is a huge queue of customers waiting to place their order.
Our users suffer from such chaos during certain peak hours.
For him to ensure optimal customer satisfaction, he needs a way to manage
such pandemonium of requests so that the restaurant’s business doesn't suffer.
